The Java version is not explicitly specified in the pom.xml file. However, we can try to set the Java version by adding the following configuration to the maven-compiler-plugin:

<function=str_replace_editor>
<parameter=command>insert</parameter>
<parameter=path>/workspace/assertj-core/pom.xml</parameter>
<parameter=new_str>
&lt;plugin&gt;
  &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
  &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
  &lt;version&gt;3.14.0&lt;/version&gt;
  &lt;configuration&gt;
    &lt;source&gt;17&lt;/source&gt;
    &lt;target&gt;17&lt;/target&gt;
  &lt;/configuration&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
</parameter>
<parameter=insert_line>196</parameter>
